Vice President Kamala Harris addressed the National Association of Counties (NACo) at the Gaylord National Convention Center in National Harbor, Maryland. She expressed her gratitude for the county leaders' hard work and dedication during the COVID-19 pandemic. Harris acknowledged the essential services provided by counties and highlighted the need for infrastructure improvements, particularly in areas like high-speed internet access. She called on county leaders to support the bipartisan infrastructure agreement and emphasized the importance of ensuring every American has access to reliable internet. Harris also discussed the right to vote, stating that protecting this right is fundamental to democracy and should be a nonpartisan issue. She acknowledged the challenges faced by local election officials and pledged to provide them with the necessary resources to carry out elections with integrity. Harris concluded her speech by thanking county leaders for their service and emphasizing their role as the first point of contact for many Americans with their government.